UDA presidential candidate William Ruto will on Wednesday take his campaigns to Murang'a county. His itinerary will start off at Kangari in Kigumo then pitch tent in Gatura in Gatanga in the afternoon. He will be accompanied by his running mate Rigathi Gachagua and other leaders allied to the party. Rigathi had on Tuesday taken his campaigns toÂ Narok and Kajiado counties. Ruto did not hold any rallies as he was preparing for presidential debate that took place at Catholic University of Eastern Africa. Azimio presidential candidate Raila Odinga will on the other hand, take the Azimio gospel to Nyeri and Laikipia counties. In Nyeri, he will address supporters in Ruringu stadium and in Laikipia he will hold the talks in Nanyuki town. Raila and his running mate Martha Karua had on Tuesday taken their campaigns to Meru county, where they explained to residents why the Azimio plan is the best to solve challenges facing the country. The two presidential candidates have intensified campaigns with just two weeks short to the August 9 General election.